=title>   To Be a Druid.  Part 3</span><hr size=1> The blue haze was beggining to fade.  My momment of peace was over.  Back to the world, where duty called to me.  I could hear noises now... noises like a battle.<br>
&quot;Not again...&quot;  I sighed.<br>
And then the scenery and the full noise crashed in around me.  I swept my eyes over the molten peaks of the lavastorm mountains.  Indeed it was a battle.<br>
&quot;How did they follow us here?!&quot;  I demanded<br>
&quot;I...do not know sir.  They appear to have a Druid in their ranks.&quot;<br>
That is when the frustration began.<br>
&quot;Why would a Druid be on their side?&quot;<br>
&quot;Tier'Dal cannot be Druids!&quot;<br>
&quot;Are Druids becomming evil?&quot;<br>
&quot;Silence!!&quot;  I shouted.  There was no way i could tell them.  Yes, there is a Tier'Dal Druid.  And he was me...in a way.  The mortal incarnation of the evil side of myself.<br>
&quot;Darkeen is here.&quot;<br>
And that was his name.  The preserver of the dark.<br>
&quot;So we will meet again, Darkeen.&quot;<br>
The voice wispered in the corner of my mind again.  &quot;You can never deafeat me.  That is because defeating me is the same as defeating yourself.&quot;  And then the charge came.<br>
Tier'Dal and Fier'Dal alike met blades.  Showing no mercy.  Blood ran on the ground.  From the back of the other line, a blast of fire shot towards us.  I did the only thing i could.<br>
A cool haze surrounded us.  And then the fire swept upon us.  The force of it pushed me back a step, but after it passed, my skin only felt sunburned.  My warrior side was always there.  Thus, i drew my scimitar and deflected a cut from a Dark elf.  I countered with a blast of wind that sent him tumbling into a pool of lava.  I watched and smiled.<br>
&quot;You drove us out of our homeland.&quot;  The only reason i had us retreat was to save what was left of Greater Faydark.  Damn the high elves.  If they had only come...when I return i will burn Felwithe to the ground, the traitors!<br>
&quot;But you will never win.&quot;  There was nothing left to be destroyed here.  I will unleash my real power.  With that, i charged.<br>
Lighting struck around me, anyone who got too close was blasted to a cinder.  I wove more resistance shields around me as i recieved the full onslaught of the enemy magic.<br>
&quot;Time to die.&quot;<br>
Flames ingulfed half the enemy ranks.  Flames that could not be quenched.  Flames that took it's time killing.  They deserved it.  Figures covered in fire ran in every direction, screaming in agony.  I heard some even call to their mothers... and loved ones.  No...Dark elves don't...<br>
The words were comming from my own mouth.  I looked down to see my hands grasping the blade of my scimitar, blood pouring over them.  Body trembling, eyes burning, i kept screaming the same name.  &quot;Catherin.&quot;<br>
<br>
FLASHBACK<br>
<br>
We stood together in the field of flowers in an embrace.  I knew then that there could be nobody else.  But what of the visions?  No, i will protect her.  With her, life had meaning again.<br>
&quot;Alexeus, you are so tence.  You need to relax for once...you are not going to get many chances.&quot;<br>
&quot;Im...sorry.  I have a lot on my mind.&quot;<br>
&quot;I believe in you, do not ever forget that.  You can do what must be done, just please, hang onto yourself.&quot;<br>
I could not do this to her.  Images dances across my vision.  Across that loving gaze.  I had to get out of here.<br>
My mind became a blur.  The only thing i could remember was my scimitar running through her chest.<br>
<br>
BACK TO PRESENT<br>
<br>
I howled at the red sky.  The enemy lines were now nothing but a twitching pile of burned bodies.  My people looked on in horror.<br>
&quot;MY FAULT!  I am just as bad as any of them!  I deserve worse!!&quot;<br>
I was in a fury.  I wanted to burn everything...now.  Someday i would die, but not before i had my vengance.  The whole world would pay.<br>
My screams continued to rip out of me, the ground shook.  Then i stopped... and looked into the distance.<br>
&quot;It is time to end it all.  We go to the Hateplane today.<br>
<br>
End of Part 3<br>
